rtitle>High Priestess of The Kindred</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/02 5:26:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cleric Ragefire List Discussion</span><hr size=1> Elaylie has asked that I moderate this forum, and I have agreed to do so. This forum was started as a service to the Drinal Cleric Community so that a current listing of clerics on the Ragefire list could always be publicly displayed. <br><br>Panamah posted this thread from Morell Thule's forum for the Ragefire list.  While there are several out there, this one is pretty well outlined and is a fair method for handling the list.  I posted the link below so that you can see how the communication flow works and how everyone seems to be doing a great job of keeping the list going and how it's working as intended.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub63.ezboard.com/fmorellthulecommunityforumsfrm60.showMessage?topicID=28.topic">pub63.ezboard.com/fmorell...D=28.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>For our purposes, I did a small bit of editing.<br><br>The short version is:<br><br>-  Have all steps of your epic completed, except RF.<br>-  Sign up here and send in screenshot of pearl, along with your e-mail addy, guild name, back-ups;<br>-  Always have someone in the RF camp;<br>-  Kill RF within 3 hours of the time it spawns;<br>-  Post here immediately after you kill RF.<br><br>The long version is:<br><br>1. The list is by Cleric, not by guild. This means if 2 clerics from the same guild are on the list, they still must complete their epic in the order they are on this list. I.E. The Flintstones have clerics at numbers 1 and 17, Betty who is number 1 is not online when Ragefire spawns, Wilma at number 17 cannot take her place in the rotation and kill Ragefire.<br><br>2. To have your name added to the list, you must have completed all other steps towards obtaining your epic and you must send a screenshot of you with the pearl to saela@eqdrinal.com prior to being added. There are NO EXCEPTIONS to this rule. Along with the pearl screenshot, you should also send in (1) your e-mail address, (2) your guild's name, and (3) a list of persons who may be contacted if you are not online.  The clerics who are currently on the list must send in this information to maintain their position on the list.<br><br>3. Always have someone in the RF camp, whether it be you or your representative.  Anyone in the RF camp should refer clerics seeking to be added to the list to this forum.<br><br>4. There is a 3 hour time limit from the moment Ragefire spawns for the first cleric on the list to kill him, during which time other forces are welcome to gather and prepare, but not engage Ragefire. If the first cleric on the list does not kill Ragefire in this time, the list's integrity should continue to be maintained by going through the list in order until a cleric who is online is in the zone and ready.  Ragefire is never FFA -- after three hours, that spawn belongs to the highest listed cleric prepared for an engagement.<br><br>5. Post here immediately after you have killed RF so that the next person on the list is notified.<br><br>6. Those clerics with * in front of their name have sent in their screenshots showing them with the pearl from Sol B.<br><br><br>This list was created to maintain civility among the guilds of Drinal.  The current listing is:<br><br>1 ramor (Winter's Light)<br>2 fierie<br>3 *feelsgood (Dark Family)<br>4 chindra<br>5 castiron<br>6 funno (Guardians of the Keep)<br>7 exidus<br>8 callandra (removed on request)<br>9 koll (Bushido Clain)<br>10 saela (The Kindred)<br>11 dolphine (Undivided Faith)<br>12 laline <br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A> at: 5/30/02 12:13:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usoftlysainteides.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SoftlySainteides</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.intelligentweb.com/myheart.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 11:07:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> I totally disagree with having ppl sign up for their ragefire camp on an ezboard.  If they want to be in on the list then they need to go to skyfire and talk to the clerics.  This is a bad idea.  I don't care for the rules either...who decided on them?  Who agreed to them?<br><br>Why can't a cleric get on the list before they have their shimmering pearl?  Who decides?<br><br>This list was made by clerics. If they want in on a list they have to do the time in Skyfire and work it out with other clerics.  Not all clerics read these boards.. not all clerics have even stepped foot in skyfire to find out who's camping and who is next etc.  <br><br>The only thing I think that should remain published here is the names of those that are on the list so there is no favoritism or bumping of members.  <br><br>My two cents.<br><br>Softly Sainteides<br>59 Cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Priestess of The Kindred</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 11:35:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> We're not re-inventing the wheel here.  This is how it's fairly done on many other servers.  The list is just starting, and while it is highly unlikely that everyone will absolutely agree with every detail, I think we can all agree on what we're trying to accomplish here.  <br><br>A link to this forum has been posted on UGoD, CiH, CT, TK, UC, WL, KC, FE, Max, and will be posted on as many guild's forums as we can find to make people aware of its existence.  In addition, the clerics who are on the list are well aware of this board's existence, and should pass that information along to any cleric who visits Skyfire and inquires about the Ragefire camp.  <br><br>Hard feelings about the list has already arisen.  If a cleric goes to Skyfire and finds a cleric on the list camping the spawn and takes the time to inquire, that cleric will be directed here, but will ultimately be the person responsible for getting his/her own name added to the list by sending in a simple e-mail.<br><br>No cleric is ready to camp Ragefire if they do not have the Swirling Pearl.  Taking the screen shot confirms that they are ready for the next step. <br><br>I don't think there's anything prejudicial about the methods for getting your name onto the list.  You can come here first, or go to Skyfire first and be told to come here.  Either way, you'll make your way to the list.  The ultimate aim is a civilized way of camping Ragefire that avoids hostility and bickering among people who would otherwise be friendly towards each other.<br><br>We are just trying to support each other and try to get all the clerics who are ready a spot.<br> 