lign=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unarvakhani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narvakhan I</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#ffcc66>Peachy</font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 12:06:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Just keep this from becoming a power trip. <p><center><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=151826"><img src="http://home1.gte.net/res0n86l/eq/ama_sig.jpg" border=0 alt="Bombadagu teh n00b"></a></p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=151826">Unconquered Plane Walker</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ukonargshaminator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Konarg Shaminator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 12:15:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ukonargshaminator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Konarg Shaminator</A> at: 5/30/02 12:18:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Priestess of The Kindred</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 12:18:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> My response below was to the previous poster (who has since edited his post) who believed that any cleric, regardless of where they were in their epic quest, should be allowed onto the list.<br><br>The other side of that coin is, since it is not likely that any cleric who is not at the Ragefire step would venture to Skyfire to inquire about the Ragefire camp (hence, learning of the list), it's prejudicial to allow anyone who is not at that stage to get on the list. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A> at: 5/30/02 12:54:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usenoramajicstarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senora Majicstarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 12:49:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> By keeping a list in an open forum, posting the rules and regulations, and keeping current updates as to each cleric's status on the list.. I think this is fair and finally a possible way to make a bad situation a bit better for everyone.<br><br>If a cleric wants his or her epic badly enough, he/she will find out about this list through friends, their guild, etc etc. If they do not have the motivation to take the steps to find out how and when to apply for the list, then I am sure there are others happy to take their spot.<br><br>Just my point of view.<br><br>Senora Majicstarr ~Oracle of Dark Family~ <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usenoramajicstarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senora Majicstarr</A> at: 5/30/02 12:50:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udirrabey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dirra Bey</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chanter's Pet</span><br>  Posts: 382<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 12:56:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pages.sbcglobal.net/mdenny/_images/ez_pic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Be careful not to bag too hard on Softly; as a cleric who already has hers now, she's obviously not prejudiced in the matter; from long experience guilding with her I know that there's no one in Norrath more generous of their time, experience, or belongings than Softly. She's just making some suggestions, and should be taken seriously. As you are of course. <br><br>Since I have no dogs in this fight (other than some former and future guildmates on the list) I think it's reasonable to have a list; it's reasonable to have to prove that you are ready for the effort and help that will go into getting it done, and it's reasonable to post it to this board; I just noticed there are over 3400 registered members here -- so it's not exactly an unknown place to post Drinal-central things. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF>