efire for anything, but would like to help once in a while if I'm on when he pops.<br><br>Edit: Discussed this with the wizards in our channel this evening.  Every wizard that was online said they would be willing to monitor and respond to a ragefire pop to help the clerics.<br><br> <p><CENTER><img src = "http://www.magetower.com/pics/gunthersig.jpg"></CENTER></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unagrak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nagrak</A> at: 5/30/02 10:14:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umagadi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>magadi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Man IN the moon</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/30/02 10:27:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Quote from Softly<br><br>"The only thing I think that should remain published here is the names of those that are on the list so there is no favoritism or bumping of members"<br><br>I agree with this completely and insistently.<br><br>The three people that originally created this list in the first place have not put their thoughts in. When we created the list in the first place we had certain things in mind. Some might agree with this, some might not, but perhaps it will put some insight into why we started this.<br><br>Heldenhammer, Emlen and I all came into skyfire at the same time to camp ragefire. (Actually, although I was ready for epic, I was actually there to support another cleric in my guild, Density, who was not online atm.) Seeing as Heldenhammer was from a former guild of mine, and I had heard about him through discussions with Density and that he had camped there with her I knew he was a good guy. Emlen helped me track the solb rage the day before, I also knew he was a good guy. Problem was, who had the rights to the camp? What did we do, we did the oldest trick in the book and rolled on it. At the time, I was rolling for my guildmate Density as she had completed all parts of her epic before me. After the worst roll ever (I believe it was a 200 500 roll and we all got under 250) I won first spawn for Density, HH won the second and Emlen the third, I would camp rage for myself after Emlen. <br><br>This was the start of the list. I hardly knew these other clerics, it wasn't me picking and choosing of my friends.<br><br>HH, Emlen and I spent about 3 weeks in skyfire together. I couldnt' ask for better cleric friends or comrades in that horrible land. As expected, clerics came and went, all wanting to camp, some more determined than others. I knew and I know there are probably hundreds of clerics on this server that are ready for this camp. Well actually every cleric is ready for this camp because it does not require a turn-in piece, but that is a separate subject all together.<br><br>My group of clerics and I talked to every single cleric that came by looking to camp. We told them how we were working it and they would have our full support if they decided to work with us and join the "list" persay. Some that weren't sure, or had thought they had been on and off camping for ragefire too long to join a list that was already 4 clerics long were not added. I understand the frustration, in retrospect I wish I had added them anyway, but there are many ways to view the situation. I'm sorry for any hard feelings that might have resulted from it.<br><br>This list of clerics for ragefire started as a private discussion between clerics that really put forth the effort in the true spirit of clericism and went to skyfire and checked with people there and actually made some very good friends out of it. This may sound mushy and girly, but I think more than half of the reason it has been successful thus far is becuase it was between the clerics that actually put forth the effort to be in skyfire for weeks on end to help others and to get the spawn for themselves. At the end of that much time you will have gotton to know some really great clerics, as an added plus, I earned the respect of the camp from other clerics mulling around and even recieved their help from their guilds when it was my turn. I even recieved the help of a guild whom I have assumed had an extreme distaste for me, that was amazing.<br><br>I would like to see the list continued, and I agree to the dismay of others I'm sure, that all parts of the epic must be done, including ixi, king note, shimmering pearl, before they will be considered for the list. I know my heart dropped to the floor when I let a cleric go ahead of me in line (none of the original three mind you) and he hadn't even done ixiblat fir yet. Those of you that have attempted the ragefire camp I think can relate to the kind of disapointment one must feel, waiting that much longer for someone not even close to done. I wouldn't ask for people to take pictures of the shimmering pearl, but that is up to the cleric currently camping ragefire in my opinion. It is their camp as far as I'm concerned.<br><br>I do want to emphasize that in order for this list to work, it cannot be impersonal. I did not want this list to be public in the first place. I thought it should be an agreement between the ones who actually came to skyfire. I see the benefits of how it could be if the one actually camping ragefire <B>tells the moderator of this board at the end of their camp </B> of the others that have stopped by showing interest and ready for ragefire.<br><br>I know I have shown alot of interest in this subject especially when I am done and over with this camp. The cleric epic is a symbol of honor among clerics and I for one know what a heartbreak it can be to fail numerous times at one or more parts of the epic. I am determined to help with whatever way I can to make this terrible camp easier for everyone involved.<br><br>-One of the original three <p><img src="http://www.crimsontwilight.org/upload/magada/option.jpg"><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211882><B>My profile   </a> --- <a href=http://www.crimsontwilight.org><B>Crimson Twilight</a></B><BR> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uluvyen666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luvyen666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/02 6:21:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Just want to say that's a great post Magada, and the input here is valuable to the understanding of how all this came to pass.<br><br>From Magada's post....<br><br>&quot; I would like to see the list continued, and I agree to the dismay of others I'm sure, that all parts of the epic must be done, including ixi, king note, shimmering pearl, before they will be considered for the list. I know my heart dropped to the floor when I let a cleric go ahead of me in line (none of the original three mind you) and he hadn't even done ixiblat fir yet. Those of you that have attempted the ragefire camp I think can relate to the kind of disapointment one must feel, waiting that much longer for someone not even close to done. I wouldn't ask for people to take pictures of the shimmering pearl, but that is up to the cleric currently camping ragefire in my opinion. It is their camp as far as I'm concerned. &quot;<br><br>The idea of having this list in the end looks to be a great idea and it will greatly alleviate the stress that many clerics have been experiencing when they come to this camp. Although I was at first against this idea, due to a misunderstanding of how it was working and that there was actually guilds available to assist the cleric on watch, I now fully support this idea. I was one of the clerics who wanted the list posted, so there is a black and white hard copy that all can see, and will be hard to change by accident or misunderstanding. <br><br>I also was one of the clerics, of which there are many, that want the list to be open to people who are ready for Ragefire, and not someone who will stuff the box in the bank for several months because they have not expended the time and effort to get to the point in the quest where they are ready for Ragefire. I really don't htink this list is any more &quot;impersonal&quot; then a word of mouth list being maintained by the clerics in SF, and it leaves no room &quot;mistakes&quot; as the list is passed down.<br><br>There is a set of rules established here, and a fixed list that is open to the public and all clerics concerned with this camp. There is support for the &quot;little guy&quot; who belongs to smaller guilds who are unable to mobilize the forces needed to take down this mob, before larger more established guilds move in and take the mob from the cleric. And the list eliminates the need for a cleric to sit with 3 or 4 other clerics at the SF camp for weeks on end, hoping and waiting for the mob to spawn. This list is a godsend to those of us still waiting to do this mob, and to those who will come later, ready to do ragefire and receive their epic. Many thanks to those &quot;original&quot; clerics who spawned this idea, and to the people who are now involved in trying to make this list a working, organized, and public information site.<br><br>It's been stated by several that the list and the way the list is being run will not be to the liking of all. You can't please all the people all of the time. However, this list is modeled after working lists on other servers, where this has worked for some time now, and I believe it will also work here.<br><br>Feelsgood Rezzman<br>60 High Priest of Dark Family  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueqdorgoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQDorgoth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/02 6:55:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> <br>Although I haven't even started on my epic yet (if I ever do) I think this list is a great idea.  I've heard the horror stories of what is happening on other servers, and I would rather not even attempt my epic than join in the whirlwind of KS'ing and ill-feelings.  This list has the potential to keep all that from coming to Drinal.<br><br>Out of curiosity though (and I know as soon as I write this that I'll find it in the first post) what happens to a cleric who for one reason or another misses their three hour window?  Do they go to the bottom of the list or remain in place and get the next spawn of RF?<br><br>Keep up the good work....I like the list!<br><br>Dorgoth da Dorf,<br>Brewmeister of White Wind <p><HTML><BODY><center><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=179411'>Dorgoth da Dorf<br>Vicar o Beer</a><p><img src='http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/2002/02/25/flamingtext_com_1014657701_31157.jpg'></center></BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udeedodevir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deedo DeVir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="h